<H3> <TI>     Reporting, Analysis on IAEA-DPRK Inspections Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   DPRK Refuses Inspections </H4>
<F P=102> AU1701202794 Paris AFP in English 1956 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1701202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Vienna, Jan 17 (AFP) -- Talks resumed Monday 
between the International Atomic Energy Agency and North Korea 
over allowing inspections of nuclear sites, with Pyongyang 
officials continuing to refuse permission, an IAEA spokesman 
said. 
  The talks are due to continue for the rest of the week. 
``The 
North Koreans put forward their points of view about future 
inspections by the IAEA, and we gave further explanations,'' 
said the spokesman. [passage omitted] 
  The spokesman said the IAEA delegation was being led by 
Demetrios Perricos and that of North Korea by Ho Jin Yun, an 
advisor to the embassy in Vienna. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-42042 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jptnd004___94061" </HT>


<HEADER>
