<H3> <TI>   Center To Train UN Chemical Weapons Inspectors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302110494 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 3 Feb 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Norbert Rief: "Austria To Train Inspectors for </F>
Chemical Weapons"] 
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- Austria will now once more participate 
in an international peacekeeping program. In the Seibersdorf 
research center, in Lower Austria, UN personnel of the 
Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) will 
be trained this year; the objective is that they can control 
civilian chemical plants. The OPCW inspectors should be able to 
find out whether chemical weapons are being or can be produced 
in chemical plants. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

