<F P=102>  BK2201085994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2201085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two unidentified armed gunmen on a motorcycle fired 
with a Kalashnikov rifle and hurled a grenade on people offering 
prayers during the Friday congregation at a mosque in Shahar 
Sultan in Muzaffargarh District yesterday. Five were killed and 
25 others injured. According to police sources, the assailants 
fled the scene soon after the incident. The police have 
barricaded Shahar Sultan to arrest the assailants. It is 
reported that additional police reinforcements have been rushed 
to Shahar Sultan from Dera Ghazi Khan, Multan, and other places 
to maintain law and order there. 

