Rome's Regina Coeli prison later in the morning, and will be 
charged with attack on public transport services. 
  A search of Mulat's luggage produced a large wooden 
crucifix, 
religious material and a notebook containing verses copied from 
the Bible, as well as photographs of the man's family. The 
hijacker told investigators that he was a Copt and was of a very 
religious nature. 
  The 43 passengers and crew on board the Ethiopian Airlines 
Boeing 757 (not 747 as stated previously) will be flown to Addis 
Ababa on the same aircraft at around midnight (2300 GMT) Monday 
