<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   9 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> PERU </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Insurgent Activities 3 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0302200094 </F>
<F P=103> PY0302200094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on insurgent activities in Peru compiled from Peruvian 
papers monitored through 3 February. 
  The Ayacucho Political-Military Command announced the arrest 
of seven "terrorists" southwest of Ayacucho Department. One of 
the main leaders has been identified as Pablo Condori Vega, 44, 
"Comrade Castro," who is considered a leader in Puquio, the 
capital of Pucanas Province. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 20 Jan 
94 p A13) 
  "Terrorists" exploded 10 kg of dynamite in downtown Huancayo 
at 1915 on 23 January in the parking lot of Hotel President, 
destroying three vehicles and seriously damaging the hotel. 
(Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 25 Jan 94 p A7) 
  General Alfredo Rodriguez Rivera, new commander of the 
Huallaga Political-Military Command, reported that 2,200 
"terrorists" who repented have surrendered in the region. They 
have asked for protection under the repentance law. Rodriguez 
added that 1,200 belong to the Tupac Amaru Revolutionary 
Movement and the rest to the Shining Path. (Lima EL COMERCIO in 
Spanish 27 Jan 94 p A11) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

