<H3> <TI>   `Extremist Elements' Blamed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2901175694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 29 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2901175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch by Randah Habib from Amman] </F>
  [Excerpt] Crown Prince Hasan has led a delegation to 
receive the body of Jordanian diplomat Na'ib 'Umran 
al-Ma'ayitah, which has arrived in Amman aboard a military 
plane, following his assassination in Beirut in front of his 
residence. The coffin, which was wrapped in the Jordanian flag, 
was taken off the plane while the members of Na'ib's family 
shouted: Allahu Akbar [God is great], O martyr of Jordan. 
  Official Jordanian sources have ruled out any personal 
motive 
behind this operation because it was carried out in an organized 
way. The Jordanian officials, who do not see any clear 
explanation for the assassination, noted that it is linked with 
extremist elements, perhaps against the background of Jordan's 
involvement in the peace process. Amman is waiting for the 
results of the ongoing investigations in Lebanon and asked to be 
briefed on the results as details are available. [passage 
omitted] 

