<H3> <TI>   Delhi Police Break Up Pakistan-Aided `Extremist Network' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0402160694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0402160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a major breakthrough Delhi Police has busted an 
extremist network with the arrest of four Punjab militants owing 
allegiance to a banned organization. One Ak-56 rifle, a Maruti 
van and 69 kg of explosives, besides 118,000 rupees in cash were 
recovered from them. Talking to newsmen in New Delhi today, the 
commissioner of police, Mr. N.B. Kaushal, said the accused 
intended to recruit youths into the gang from states outside 
Punjab and motivate them to strike at VIP's and important 
installations. He said the group was being funded by Pakistan's 
ISI [Inter-Service Intelligence] to carry out terrorist 
activities in India. 

</TEXT>

