<H3> <TI>   Three Israelis Wounded by Shots From Passing Car </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0202131094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 2 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0202131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Three Israelis were wounded by terrorist gunfire 
in Halhul a short while ago. One of them is in critical 
condition and the other two in moderate condition. Our 
correspondent Moti Amir reports that as a Subaru passed the 
three men's car at the entrance to Halhul from the direction of 
Hebron, some 20 bullets were fired from it. A leaflet signed by 
the 'Izz al-Din al-Qassam squad was found on the site. The 
Subaru was later found abandoned in Hebron. The security forces 
have clamped a curfew on the area. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

