<H3> <TI>   Security Agencies Investigate Amman Theater Explosion </TI></H3>
<H4>   Seven Arrested; Motive Unknown </H4>
<F P=102> JN0302093594 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 3 Feb 94 pp 1, 20 </F>
<F P=103> JN0302093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Khulud al-Ja'uni] </F>
  [Excerpt] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has stated that 
seven people were detained for interrogation in connection with 
the bomb blasts in Salma cinema house in al-Zarqa' and the 
Rivoli cinema house in Saqf al-Sayl Street in downtown Amman. 
He said some of these people were released after interrogation. 
  Hammad said that the dimensions and motives for the two 
blasts are still unknown. 
  Meanwhile, a team set up by various security agencies is 
continuing its investigation to identify the perpetrators of the 
bomb blast that occurred in Salwa cinema house in al-Zarqa' the 
day before yesterday. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

