Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has stated that 
the criminals who planted explosives at the Cinema Rivoli in 
Amman, Cinema Salwa in al-Zarqa', and the al-'Akrush Supermarket 
in the town of Safut have been apprehended. The explosive 
charge planted in Safut was discovered and defused, he noted. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency, Petra, the 
interior minister added: Muhammad 'Ali Shihadah, alias 
Abu-'Abbad, a construction worker aged 26 years, and 'Id Salih 
al-Jahalin, a plumber aged 31 years, have admitted that they 
committed these crimes. They are part of a group that will be 
uncovered later. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

