<H3> <TI>   Update on French Hostages Held by Tribe </TI></H3>
<H4>   Minister on `Practical Measures' To Free Hostages </H4>
<F P=102> JN3101155994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1514 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3101155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yemeni Minister of Interior Brigadier General Yahya 
al-Mutawakkil has denied that the kidnapping of three French 
nationals northwest of Sanaa last week was politically motivated. 
  In press statements today, he added that the kidnappers 
motive in taking the three hostages, one man and two women, is 
to provoke the government and make unrealistic demands. He went 
on to say that his ministry has taken practical measures to 
besiege the kidnappers in case they do not surrender and free 
the hostages. 

</TEXT>

