<H3> <TI>   `Retribution' Group Threatens To Blow Up Yakutsk Vital Facilities </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ransom Demanded </H4>
<F P=102> LD0202134494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Retribution [Vozmezdiye] terrorist group has 
demanded that the Yakutsk authorities hand over $500,000 and 500 
million rubles at the city's airport on 4 February. Otherwise 
they are threatening to blow up facilities providing vital 
services to the capital of Yakutia. According to INTERFAX, a 
cassette recording with these demands was handed in to the 
mayor's office by an unidentified person. Employees of the 
Ministries of Security and Internal Affairs are searching for 
the criminals. 

</TEXT>

