<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Retribution' Group Threatens To Blow Up Yakutsk Vital Facilities </TI></H3>
<H4>   Yakutsk, Moscow Pool CT Efforts </H4>
<F P=102> LD0302182994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1604 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 3 TASS -- Operational headquarters 
has been formed in Yakutsk, capital of Russia's northeast 
Siberian autonomy, to deal with emergencies, including acts of 
terror, the press service of the Federal Ministry for 
Emergencies told ITAR-TASS on Thursday. 
  The headquarters will include members of the Federal 
Interior 
Ministry, the Federal Counter-Intelligence Service, the Federal 
Prosecutor's Office and the Federal Committee for Emergencies, 
as well as Moscow officials. 
  As is known, terrorists from the Vozmezdie (Retribution) 
group have demanded that the Yakutsk authorites hand over to 
them US$500,000 and 500 million rubles at Yakutsk Airport on 
February 4. The terrorists threaten to explode the city's life 
supporting installations if their demand is not met. 
  Experts of the Russian Interior Ministry believe that the 
threat of the explosion is no more than a bluff since the 
criminals need only money. Moreover, competent bodies together 
with army specialists are carrying out operational measures to 
locate and defuse any possible explosive devices. 
  The Trans-Baikal regional centre of the Federal Ministry for 
Emergencies has been put on red alert. Rescue teams are on 
board an aircraft at a Moscow airport, ready to take off for 
Yakutsk any time. 

</TEXT>

