<H3> <TI>   Man Takes 4 Hostages for Ransom in Sukhodolsk </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Terrorist,' Hostages Head for Rostov, Aircraft </H4>
<F P=102> LD0302151794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1322 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text) Moscow February 3 TASS -- On Thursday, a terrorist 
seized two children, their teacher and the driver of a van on 
Thursday [as received] in the Ukrainian city of Sukhodolsk in 
Lugansk region and is demanding US$500,000 ransom, a pistol and 
a plane. 
  The kidnapper, who was identified as Nikolay Skvortsov a 
resident of Sukhodolsk, is holding a grenade with a pulled-out 
pin in his hand [as received] and threatens to explode it if his 
demands are not met, TASS was told at the Russian Ministry for 
Emergency Situations. 
  Currently, Skvortsov with his hostages is going on the van 
to 
the Russian city of Rostov-on-Don where a plane is being 
prepared for him and anti-terrorist groups are ready. 
  The pistol which he received in Ukraine was out of order and 
he threw it away. 

</TEXT>

