<H3> <TI>   Basque ETA Suspected of Rome Bomb Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0302145794 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1255 GMT 3 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BR0302145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Paper Bomb at Spanish Embassy"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 3 Feb (ANSA) -- Early results of an analysis 
of the bomb remnants indicated that only part of it, around the 
detonator, exploded. If this is confirmed by investigators, it 
would represent a major change in the scale and direction of 
terrorist violence against Spanish targets in Rome, experts said. 
  The probable target of the attack was the owner of the car, 
Spanish military attache Ruano Fernando Sagristano, 
investigators say--raising the hypothesis that the persons who 
planted the bomb meant to kill him. 
  As to the authors, they pointed to the Basque terrorist 
organisation, ETA, which has been responsible for a string of 
largely symbolic bomb attacks in Rome, against property rather 
than individuals. 

</TEXT>

