Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Malatya, Feb 3 (AA) -- Seventeen terrorists 
belonging to an outlawed leftist terrorist organization were 
captured following security operations in southeastern Malatya 
Province, it was reported on Thursday. 
  A written statement from Malatya Mayor's Office said the 
terrorists were captured following joint operations by security 
headquarters and the gendarmerie forces to the terrorists 
safe-houses in the city. 
  Firearms, ammunitions and money were seized following the 
searches of the safe-house, it added. 

