<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   9 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jerusalem Advised of Iranian Plan To Base Terror in Cyprus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0402120494 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 4 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> TA0402120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv MA'ARIV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hemi Shalev] </F>
  [Text] The Cypriot security services suspect that Iran is 
trying to set up a regional command in Cyprus to organize Iran's 
terrorist activities in Lebanon and other Middle East countries. 
The conclusions of the Cypriot security services' investigation 
on this matter have been recently conveyed to Jerusalem. 
  The Cypriot authorities have recently taken action to foil 
the Iranian plans. Among other actions, they prohibited the 
entry of several Iranian citizens to the island. 
  According to Jerusalem, Israel "monitors" the developments 
and is in close contact with the Cypriot authorities. The 
investigation conducted by the Cypriot security services showed 
that Iranians have recently purchased houses in Cyprus. In 
addition, lively traffic has been noticed between the two 
countries. A probe revealed that a plan to make Cyprus a terror 
base was behind these phenomena. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
